jibe.sdk.client.simple
Interface ChallengeDialog.Listener

Enclosing class:
ChallengeDialog
public static interface ChallengeDialog.Listener

Callback interface to notify the application of the user's choice. Note that the dialog is automatically dismissed when any of the callback methods is invoked.

Method Summary
 void onAccepted(ChallengeDialog source, Intent intent)
          Invoked if the user presses the accept button.
 void onError(ChallengeDialog source, int reason)
          Invoked if an error occurs before the user accepts or rejects.
 void onRejected(ChallengeDialog source)
          Invoked if the user presses the reject button.
 

Method Detail

onAccepted

void onAccepted(ChallengeDialog source,
                Intent intent)
Invoked if the user presses the accept button. Note that the incoming connection still needs to be accepted explicitly. The dialog itself is dismissed automatically.

Parameters:
source - Source of the user input
intent - Intent of the connection which has been accepted

onRejected

void onRejected(ChallengeDialog source)
Invoked if the user presses the reject button. Note that the incoming connection has already been rejected in this case and that no further connection handling is necessary. The dialog itself is dismissed automatically.

Parameters:
source - Source of the user input

onError

void onError(ChallengeDialog source,
             int reason)
Invoked if an error occurs before the user accepts or rejects. In most cases this means that either the challenging party has chosen to cancel the challenge or that the challenge has timed out. Note that the connection has been cleaned up in this case and cannot be rejected or accepted anymore. The dialog itself is dismissed automatically.

Parameters:
source - Source of the user input
reason - Reason for the failure as defined in JibeSessionEvent
